[MK] case called at 3:04pm. 
Defendant Tracey E Winter in court with Attorney Yelena O. Zarwell.  ADA Theresa Beck appears for the State of Wisconsin.  
Ms. Winter verifies that the date of birth and address on the Criminal Complaint are accurate.
Service of the Criminal Complaint admitted; the charge and maximum penalties are recited; the reading of the factual portion of the Criminal Complaint is waived. 
Ms. Winter waives her right to Preliminary Hearing; the Court accepts this waiver and binds her over for Trial.
Service of Information admitted, reading waived
Constitutional rights reviewed; plea of " No Contest " entered; factual basis stipulated; victim rights compliance verified; the Court accepts the plea, finds Ms. Winter guilty, and orders Judgment of Conviction entered.

The Court withholds sentence, and places Ms. Winter on Probation for two years, with conditions:
--Ms. Winter is not to volunteer or have employment that involves working with vunerable adults or children
--to undergo any assessment, treatment, or counseling as deemed appropriate by the Agent
--to obtain/maintain employment and/or education program consistentas approved by the Agent
--to provide a DNA sample to the Jefferson County Sheriff before any return to the State of Colorado under the Interstate Compact 
--to pay costs of $268 plus the $250 DNA surcharge
